[NPC] Sharven: Have a couple of travel tokens to speed things up.

[To] Chired Idelall

[NPC Internal] Sharven sent me.
[NPC] Chired: Ah yes, child, I've been expecting you.
[NPC] Chired: Vladovic was just here and we have prepared a Life Elixir which should be ready any minute.
[NPC] Chired: I feel the burden of Dakkru's curse upon your body, but your soul has been purified.
[NPC] Chired: The special ingredient Sharven needs is an Essence of Happiness.
[NPC] Chired: For that I will need a very special component: a drop of your blood.
[NPC Narrate] Chired Idelall takes your hand and swiftly pricks your finger, extracting a small drop of blood.
[NPC] Chired: You already know how to extract essences from blood and from your blood I will extract the Essence of Happiness now that your soul is lighter than a kikiri feather and your body was purified by dying.
[NPC Internal] You mean I have to die every time I want to make one of these potions?
[NPC Narrate] Chired Idelall chuckles.
[NPC] Chired: No, don't worry.
[NPC] Chired: This is a very unique case.
[NPC] Chired: This is an extension of the Great Work we are trying here.
[NPC] Chired: It will not be necessary once you begin the Great Work for yourself, but it is good to understand these connections so you can appreciate the various stages.
[NPC] Chired: Now let's get to work.
[NPC Narrate] Chired Idelall puts your blood into the alembic then carefully mixes some reagents in other vials. She then mixes it together and puts it in the decanter. She waits a moment, then carefully mixes it together with another potion on the table with a stirrer. Finally, she meticulously measures it and pours it into a vial, sealing it with a cork.
[NPC] Chired: There, all done.
[NPC] Chired: Now take this quickly back to Sharven.
[NPC Narrate] Chired Idelall hands you the vial.
[NPC Internal] You got anything to lift this curse?
[NPC Narrate] Chired Idelall laughs.
[NPC] Chired: I'm afraid not.
[NPC] Chired: Even the Great Work cannot compete with Dakkru's power.

[To] Sharven Xant-Areth

[NPC Internal] I have the cure! [You hand Sharven the vial.]
[NPC Narrate] Sharven Xant-Areth's eyes widen and he breaks into a wide grin.
[NPC] Sharven: Wonderful!
[NPC] Sharven: You did it, YOU.
[NPC] Sharven: I knew you would come through!
[NPC] Sharven: I know you have been through a lot, but now I hope you are beginning to understand the nature of the Great Work and how special it is.
[NPC] Sharven: It is deeply rooted in Lemur culture and history but now it is available to all.
[NPC] Sharven: I shall get this to Charisa immediately.
[NPC] Sharven: Thank you and may Laanx always frighten the shadow from thy path.
[NPC Narrate] Sharven Xant-Areth hands you a very large pouch of tria.
[NPC] Sharven: And remember, Vladovic will have much more to teach you.

